	<Title>
		Healthy meal planning for 1
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Meal planning for weight loss can be more challenging when you&apos;re cooking only for yourself. You may be faced with lots of leftovers or have to toss out uneaten food. Use these tips to stay on track: 1. Cook a batch and freeze single portions. 2. Prepare one-dish meals, such as stews and casseroles. 3. Carry it forward by using leftovers in a new dish later in the week, such as using rice as a side dish one day and the extra in a yummy rice pudding dessert the next.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
